name: Interzone Cafe
directions: Enter the front door, pass the counter Ã‘ it's in the back. Place has great coffee and vegetarian/vegan food as well. The staff is pretty chill, so if you don't buy anything, you'll probably be okay.
comment: Open 7 am to midnight weekdays and 8 am to midnight on weekends. Summer hours close at 10 pm.

name: Pride Center
directions: Small building on OSU's campus with friendly staff and resources for LGBTQQI folk and allies. Building has a ramp.
comment: Hours during school year are usually 10-5 or 10-6. Limited summer hours.

name: Epic Cafe
directions: In Back CornerGrab the rubber chicken keychain on the hook by the counter
comment: Great Vegan Food and Desserts.. They make Great Coffee as well..!!

name: Watson Hall Syracuse University
directions: swipe your card to get into the building or if its before 8pm wait til someone opens the door. Take a left and go through a set of doors, pass one room on the right, and immediately on either side of you will be two labelled all-gender single stall restrooms. They include locks.
comment: They're supposed to be adding in an all-gender multi-stall restroom somewhere in the building eventually.

name: Vynl
comment: Four cleverly themed restrooms. Though intended for use by any sex, all have the names of female gay-appeal divas (Cher, Dolly, etc.), play the diva's music in the single stall, and have a little shrine.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Near front, through a door on the south wall behind the cash registers
comment: open 8 a.m.-9 p.m. daily

name: Fallons Furniture
directions: Rear of first floor showroom.

name: La-z-boy Furniture Galleries
directions: Enter through main entrance, proceed to Northwest Corner of building.
comment: open 9-5 mtwt 9-9 fs 12-6 sunday

name: Quad Cycles
directions: In the back, up the stairs, last door on the left.
comment: It's a bike shop, open most days.

name: Southern Nights
directions: On the left side of the stage in the theater side. Two single-stall, locking, non-gendered rooms.

name: Gates Computer Science Building
directions: 5th floor
comment: The Gates Building is open during the week, during normal business hours. These two bathrooms on the fifth floor might be locked?

name: Frisson Restaurant
comment: New Restaurant, co-ed bathrooms.

name: Emanon
directions: Straight back opposite the bar

name: Ethiopia Restaurant
directions: in the front room.

name: Shalimar
directions: in the way back. two, locking single stall gendered bathrooms.
comment: occasionally one or the other appears to be broken, in which case people use either or. rather isolated from the restaurant.

name: Zeitgeist Bar
directions: there are three, two inside near where you order food. and one, the porta-potty in the beer garden!
comment: must be over 21. mixed queer straight hipster bike messenger crowd.

name: Wharf Taqueria & Cafe
directions: by the computer. needs a key you can get at the counter
comment: cheap purchases including water and chips. a relief when you're trapped in the wharf

name: Ritual Roasters
directions: in the way back to the right.
comment: crowd can be very hipstery.

name: Autumn Leaves Bookstore
directions: It's in the back near the kids section on the first floor. Just walk in the door or ask staff if you have trouble finding it.
comment: Ithaca is usually a safe place for GLBT people. And many of the businesses are GLBT friendly.

name: Belmont library
directions: They now have keys by the front check out desks that you have to use.
comment: Monday: 10 a.m.-6 p.m.Tuesday & Wednesday: noon-8 p.m.Thursday-Saturday: 10 a.m. - 6 p.m.Sunday: noon-5 p.m.

name: Holgate library
comment: Monday: 10 a.m.-6 p.m.Tuesday & Wednesday: noon-8 p.m.Thursday-Saturday: 10 a.m.-6 p.m.Sunday: noon-5 p.m

name: Jimmy Tingle's off broadway
directions: basement
comment: the one by the box office is ungendered. the others in the back are gendered

name: Grants Pass Rogue Community College Q Building
directions: Front entrance right off of Redwood Highway (Different from Redwood Ave.) there is the daycare building to the left of a cluster of buildings (P and Q etc.) In Q-2, a classroom, there is a large, gender free bathroom, single stall but spacious.
comment: RCC-RWC Q building open from 7:30am-5pmClassroom isnt' constantly in use, but it is from time to time. You aren't going to get checked for ID to use a bathroom though. ^_~

name: Clackamas Community College
directions: One in DeJardin Hall and one in Niemeyer hall.
comment: Technically supposed to be a student, but act like you know what you're doing and no one will ask.

name: Pad Thai Cafe
directions: Right past the counter.
comment: Pretty much 11:30am - 11pmThey are super nice and have always been amazingly polite to visibly queer folks. Right around the corner from Fenway Community Health. Also the food is great.

name: Java Monkey
directions: inside the coffee shop, in the back. there are two single occupancy locked bathrooms. one says 'guys/girls' and the other says 'girls/guys'

name: Clarke's At Faneuil Hall
directions: The place isn't in the arcade that is described as Faneuil Hall it's just outside.  It's on the corner of Chatham Street, near Plaza III (which is in the arcade.Go in from the entrance at the corner, and walk to the left of the bar, it's all the way in the back.  The door is on the right.  There are other bathrooms on the other side downstairs, these are gendered.
comment: In the evening they card, it's a pretty happening place for drinks after work.  During the day it's a lot slower, tourists and locals eating lunch.  It's a nice place to grab a quick pub lunch.

name: Flying Pie Pizzeria
directions: The place is a bit of a maze and there may be multiple bathrooms, but for sure there's a unisex one off the back room (the room farthest east from the entrance, or nearest the movie theater next door). Look for the sign that says Restrooms.

name: McKinley Hall
directions: go up the steps into the building turn right after going through the second set of doors...right near room 101
comment: Pretty clean most of the time!!

name: whole foods
directions: Del Monte Plaza
comment: it's whole foods, but the bathrooms are back by the fish and meat counters!2 - single stall bathrooms, one labled women, one gender free.

name: It's a Grind
directions: in the back
comment: open late

name: Bar 303
directions: Walk straight through building, past the bar, down the stairs, down past the left of the stage.

name: Laughing Horse Books
directions: In the back, on the left!

name: Viva! Taqueria & Cantina
directions: It's in the back of the main dining area, on the left.

name: Yakuza
directions: Straight back behind the main section, to the left

name: Haymarket
directions: Downstairs
comment: 2, single-stall bathrooms.  Both big enough for wheelchairs but I'm not sure that the downstairs of Haymarket has a wheelchair entrance.  It might in the back of the building.

name: Black Sheep Deli
directions: First floor. Across from Amherst Chinese Food, just downhill from the Commons.
comment: Two locking, single-stall, non-gendered bathrooms. Not accessible: Two steps down to get to them.

name: Rao's coffee shop
directions: Next to Panda East, behind the Unitarian church, adjacent to the big municipal parking lot. First floor.
comment: open til 11 on weekends. four restrooms are all single-stall, locking, non-gendered. two of four are pretty accessible - no automatic doors, but plenty of room to turn around. the other two are in a narrow hallway, but also accesible for a small wheelchair. one is painted with blackboard paint and chalk is available for you to draw/write on the walls while you pee.

name: Thayer Building, University of Michigan
directions: On the first floor, on the right, past the offices, by the elevator.
comment: On campus directions can be found here: http://uuis.umich.edu/cic/buildingproject/index.cfm?BuildingID=524

name: Onsite Computer Solutions
comment: Talk to Shawn, Lance or Ian and ask for use. Its a one room office with a single bathroom.

name: The Coffee Mill
directions: First floor, straight through the cafe in the back.
comment: They have some interesting flavors of coffee.

name: Venice Boardwalk Public Bathrooms
directions: There are public bathrooms every so often at the beach along the boardwalk in Venice, they are all single stall, genderfree bathrooms.
comment: The bathrooms are open dawn to dusk

name: Home Depot
directions: Family Bathroom: From the front door, all the way to the back then turn left. It's on your right next to the other bathrooms.
comment: They'll ask you if they can help. Ask for the bathroom, they're more than happy to direct you.

name: Rosetta's Kitchen
comment: They actually have 2 gender neutral restrooms in this restaurant!

name: Wild Side West
directions: in the back room of the indoor area. gendered but people seem to use either.

name: Lexington Bar
directions: two bathrooms towards the rear by the juke box.
comment: yay san francisco's dyke bar.

name: Women & Children First Bookstore
directions: back of the store, under exit sign

name: Allan Brothers Coffee
directions: by the shelves

name: LCC Health Center
comment: Technically, only for people with appointments at the health center

name: Sweetlife
comment: There is one gender-neutral bathroom and one women's bathroom.

name: Espresso Roma
directions: Gendered bathrooms are outside in the back, the genderfree bathroom is in the back of the large side room, which is opposite the register.

name: north face store
directions: second floor towards the back corner. no key.
comment: just pretend that you're looking at jackets and you should be okay.

name: East Side Pockets
directions: In the back.  I think there's a sign saying no bathroom is available, but it's lying.
comment: You may have to buy something to avoid annoying the owners, but that's okay because this is one of the best places to eat in the area.  Try the spinach pie and falafel ;-)Regular single-stall locking bathroom.

name: Bradley Barber Shop
comment: Regular single-stall bathroom.

name: Capitol Hill Presbyterian Church
directions: Up the stairs outside the sanctuary.
comment: Sorry, I don't know when/how the bathroom is available.  It's a single stall and does not have a lock.

name: AT&T Park
directions: Family bathrooms with locking doors are located throughout the park.

name: Kimo's Bar
directions: first floor towards the back

name: Academy Hall
directions: 1) 2nd floor2) 4th floor, near FYE office

name: RPI Student Union
directions: 1) 1st floor, inside Mother's, 'dressing room'2) 2nd floor, inside 2424
comment: RPI union technically only open to students/staff and guests, but nobody checks

name: Java++
directions: walk through the cafe, bear right (towards the glass). very friendly.

name: Lakeforest Mall
directions: 1st floor near Sears
comment: "family restroom"

name: Jo-Ann Fabric and Craft Store
directions: towards the back left

name: Lucky Monkey
directions: back hallway; reserved for Lucky Monkey customers.

name: Alaska Visitors Center
directions: First floor bathrooms are single-stall, but the outside doors don't lock without a key.

name: Gay & Lesbian Community Center of Anchorage
Cold Stone Creamery
directions: towards the back
comment: near cleveland park metro

name: Smithsonian National Museum of Natural History
directions: 1st floor, near the other restrooms

name: Cedar Lane Unitarian Universalist Church
directions: Main building, downstairs next to 3rd grade classroom
comment: church is officially Welcoming of LGBT people

name: Stony Brook Community Church
directions: basement of church, in back (there's an elevator from the ground floor)
comment: United Methodist church

name: Cheng Chen Chinese Restaurant
directions: back left corner of building

name: The Flying Burrito
directions: towards the back, behind the rice curtain

name: Department of Women's Studies, University of Arizona
directions: First floor: walk past the staircase, it will be your first door on your left.Second floor: go up the stairs, go right at the fork, follow the hallway all the way to the end.

name: Lime Kiln Cafe
directions: outside the actual cafe
comment: 6 of them; 1 is accessible

name: Lady Of The Lake boat company dock
directions: in the building to the right of people standing in line

name: Capitol Building
directions: On the 4th floor of the legislative building near the house/senate galleries
comment: family restroom

name: Science Fiction Museum
directions: 1 each on 1st floor and 2nd floor

name: The Space Needle
directions: on the O deck level
comment: labelled as a Family Restroom;it costs Money to get into the space needle

name: Christ Congregational Church
directions: 1st floor, opposite church office

name: St. Paul's UMC
directions: 1st floor

name: Bently's House of Coffee and Tea
directions: If you go in the east entrance the bathroom is to your left.

name: Christ Church
directions: If you go up the stairs - the set in the middle of the building, not by the door - it's off the landing.
comment: United Methodist church

name: Grace United Methodist Church
directions: Directly across the lobby from the Walker Ave. entrance
comment: 2 of them: one on the left has a stall, one on the right is single-user and locking

name: Doug Fir Lounge
directions: In the foyer, on the right when entering the building/ left when coming from the restaurant.
comment: Single stall gender-neutral, usually quite clean for a bar bathroom!, no key.

name: Green Beans Coffee
directions: You get a key from the cafe, walk out behind the counter, and go up a couple of steps outside.
comment: Single stall; has a multi-gender bathroom sign with the pants figure labeled "Women" and the skirt figure labeled "Men."  I feel loved every time I look at it.

name: Wooden Shoe Books
directions: radical bookstore. Very nice. One bathroom free for all, in back of store on the right.

name: Open Eye Cafe
directions: To the right of the counter.

name: Unity House
directions: 2nd floor
comment: They run a "safety zone" drop-in programme for LGBT teens

name: Strathmore Hall
directions: In the mansion, near the gift shop
comment: 2 of themI ~think~ they're accessible, not sure tho (unmarked)

name: Trader Joe's
directions: Towards the back, near the unrefrigerated soymilk

name: Flavor Cafe
directions: Walk in like you're going to the patio (opposite the front door) and it's around the corner right before you run into the patio door.
comment: I'm not sure whether they care if you use the bathroom without buying anything.

name: Southern Kitchen
directions: back of restaurant

name: Tully's Coffee
directions: to the right and back
comment: need a key that you can get at the counter

name: North Portland Library
directions: One on the main floor near the reference desk, one upstairs outside the meeting room. Key on big tag at the reference desk.
